{
  "texts": [
    "Ultimately, ChronoLLM is meant to assist the users in generating PyChrono scriptsthe users are not interested if their request is in-distribution or not.",
    "Ideally, ChronoLLM would be trained on an amount of data that would make any request in-distribution.",
    "This is not possible, and we argue that it is not necessary.",
    "Even providing a good starting point for the users is a gain.",
    "First Case Study: Double Pendulum SimulationWe start with an easy request to generate a double pendulum -asking the pretrained LLM to generate the pyChrono script without giving any specific setting of the two bodies, e.g."
  ]
}